# Code Review Report: x.jsx

## Summary
Scoped review only for Batch 9 regressions Fix 1-3 in `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx`, using `pages/PublicMenu/README.md`, `pages/PublicMenu/BUGS.md`, and local `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx` as context. All three requested regressions are still present in the current file.

## Findings
1. [P2] Fix 1 not applied: table confirmation Bottom Sheet still pushes browser history before opening the Drawer. In [`x.jsx`](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L2749), `pushOverlay('tableConfirm')` still precedes `setShowTableConfirmSheet(true)`, while `pushOverlay` itself mutates history synchronously at [`x.jsx`](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L1305). FIX: reverse the order and defer `pushOverlay('tableConfirm')` until after render; do not change the existing `onOpenChange` cleanup at [`x.jsx`](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L3533).
2. [P2] Fix 2 not applied: the help bell remains gated behind table verification. The condition at [`x.jsx`](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L3838) still requires `isTableVerified && currentTableId`, so the bell is absent in hall mode before table verification. FIX: gate on `view === "menu" && isHallMode && drawerMode !== 'cart'` instead.
3. [P3] Fix 3 not applied: the help drawer still lacks the top-right ChevronDown close control. [`x.jsx`](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L3651) does not include `relative` on `DrawerContent`, and no chevron button using `closeHelpDrawer` is rendered inside the drawer. FIX: add `relative` and insert the same gray circular chevron button used by the table-code drawer.

## Verification Notes
- `TableConfirm` drawer close logic already pops overlay on close at [`x.jsx`](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L3533), so Fix 1 should stay limited to open timing.
- `closeHelpDrawer` already exists at [`x.jsx`](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L1654), so Fix 3 only needs wiring plus positioning.
- Independent `codex exec` review could not be completed in this environment: the CLI returned `os error 5` (`Access is denied`).
